Defendant Justin M Sinnen in court with attorney Matthew Russell Meyer.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.

Statements made as to sentencing.
AMENDED COUNT 2 & 3 - CONCURRENT:
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served.  Huber privileges for work and/or school.   No electronic monitoring.   

COUNT 1 - CONCURRENT:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS with credit for 2 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.  The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and IS NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCES and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 4 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION/PROBATION:
* Court ordered the defendant to serve 45 DAYS
   in the House of Correction.  STAYED.  To be used at agent's discretion.
* Continue with counseling.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
   and successfully complete recommended treatment. (IF WARRANTED BY AGENT)
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol. (IF WARRANTED BY AGENT)
* No contact with the victim(s) without prior court/agent approval.  Any violation may result in additional charges.	
* Obtain GED/HSED.
* No firearms; weapons.
* Obtain and maintain employment and/or school and/or vocational training.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

The Court ordered that all court costs, fees, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Court does not order sex registry.
